<div type="history" n="text-constituted-from">
<head>Text Constituted From</head>
<p>Preliminary transcription (Reynolds); publications.</p>
</div>

<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>Cl<supplied reason="abbreviation">audia</supplied> Antonia</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>Robert suggested that the donor might be Claudia Antonia Tatiana; but there is no clear support for this.</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p>
Original location: <rs type="origLocation">Findspot</rs>;
Found: <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">South Agora</rs>, north portico: i Column 18, ii column 19, iii apparently from column 20, from east end</rs>; Last known location: <rs type="lastLocation">Findspot</rs>
</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="record">
<head>History of Recording</head>
<p>i. and ii copied by K&amp;R, 'southern portico' (iii.38); i and ii recorded by the Italian Mission; i, ii and iii recorded by the NYU expedition.</p>
</div>
